<BaseLayout title="Stochastic Gauge Hodge Theory | Muhammad Umar Javed">
  <section class="content">
    <section>
      <h2>Publications</h2>
      <div class="list">
        <article class="list-item">
          <h3>Too Free to Be Free: Non-Ergodicity of Harmonic Entanglement on Random Gauged Hodge Laplacians</h3>
          <p class="muted">MU Javed. Manuscript.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Summary Overview</h2>
      <p>This theme studies random gauged Hodge structures, harmonic entanglement, and non-ergodic behavior in geometric systems with hidden constraints. The work asks how much structure remains visible when randomness is shaped by gauge transport, Hodge Laplacians, and harmonic subspaces.</p>
      <p>The current focus is theoretical: understanding when apparent freedom in random geometric systems still produces persistent structure, rigidity, or obstruction to ergodic mixing.</p>
    </section>
  </section>
